pes=3D"Picture_x0020_1"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Taxes on your empire&#8217;s
colonies are your primary source of income.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
he
population of each colony goes about their private business, generating wea=
lth.
Your empire then taxes this revenue generated by your private citizens.<o:p=
></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
his
relationship of private revenue to state tax revenue is shown in the Economy
section of the Empire Summary screen (F6). The &#8220;Annual Income&#8221; =
row
shows how much state &#8220;Colony Tax Revenue&#8221; you make from the pri=
vate
&#8220;Colony Revenue.&#8221;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>P=
rivate
colony income is calculated as follows:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-indent:.5in'><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-s=
tyle:normal'><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Colony Income =3D Total Popu=
lation
&times; Development Level<o:p></o:p></span></i></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
his
private colony income is what your empire taxes, generating income for your
empire. Thus to maximize tax revenue you must help grow your colonies,
maximizing both the population and development of each colony.<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>

<p class=3DHeading3new><span lang=3DEN-GB>Setting tax rates</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>C=
olony tax
rates can be set anywhere from zero up to 50%. If the citizens at the colony
think the tax rate is too high this will lower their approval of you, making
them unhappier.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Y=
ou can opt
to have your colony tax rates controlled automatically (the default setting=
).
In this case the rate will be set at an appropriate level for the size and
development of the colony.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DHeading3new><span lang=3DEN-GB>Taxes and Colony Growth</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>W=
hen a
colony is first established the tax rate is usually very low. This makes the
colony&#8217;s population happier and encourages faster growth.<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>A=
s a colony
grows in size and development, the tax rate can be increased and you can st=
art
earning decent tax income from the colony.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>H=
owever as
the colony grows even further, its citizens will develop a level of resista=
nce
to paying high taxes. Thus the acceptable tax rate will fall. This resistan=
ce
usually coincides with a large increase in colony revenue, so the actual am=
ount
of tax income from the colony does not drop. But resistance to paying high
taxes puts an effective cap on how much tax revenue you can get from a sing=
le
colony.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>O=
nce your
colony reaches a size of one billion citizens an unavoidable level of
corruption will also begin, further reducing how much tax you collect from =
the
colony. Some types of government can reduce this corruption and tax evasion=
.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DHeading3new><span lang=3DEN-GB>Other factors</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>S=
ome alien
races are &#8220;Natural Merchants&#8221;, meaning that their colonies gene=
rate
more income. This means greater private revenue, thus more tax income for y=
our
empire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>S=
ome types
of government also have a natural trade bonus that increases colony income,=
 and
thus tax income.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

